The first made-in-China cruise ship suitable for the rough waters around the Antarctic leaves its shipyard in Nantong, East China's Jiangsu Province, bound for Ushuaia, Argentina. The 8,000-ton ship can carry 254 passengers and can withstand the toughest sailing conditions. It also has very high standards of environmental friendliness. Photo: VCG
